JOHANNESBURG - Ekurhuleni Mayors Mzwandile Masina's stern warning on Monday, to white South Africans and the Save South Africa campaign has been met with outrage.Masina launched a scathing attack against anti-Zuma protesters, saying they are against nation-building. He then also promised consequences for any mass action against the president.WATCH: Ekurhuleni mayor issues warning to white South AfricansThe DA has referred Masina to the metro's ethics and integrity committee for what it calls his anti-white comments.The opposition says his remarks violate the constitution -- which gives people the right to protest.The Save South Africa Campaign has also condemned the comments made by Masina at a Chris Hani lecture last night:eNCA